 Obituary: June 2010, San Francisco Chronicle. Obituary for Jerome Warren "Jerry" Pribyl:

Jerry was born in Monticello, Minnesota on November 1, 1920. He is survived by sisters Catherine (Peter) Lupori of Minneapolis and Helen (Jerry) Bailey of Aurora, Colorado. He is also survived by his much loved wife, Peggy Pribyl. They celebrated their 65th wedding anniversary last year. Jerry had seven daughters and six sons. They are: Wesley Ann (Jones), Gregory Michael, Terese Marie (Sciabica), David Warren, Stephen Jerome, Daniel John, Mary Catherine (Sondgroth), Margaret Jane Marie (Oberg), Virginia Louise (Saiz), Laura Jean (Coger), Clare Antoinette (Pryden), Thomas Damien and Anthony Joseph. He was a loving grandfather to thirty-nine grandchildren and twenty three great grandchildren. Jerry was a WWII veteran and recipient of the US Army's Purple Heart. He was wounded during the North Africa Campaign. He settled in the Bay Area after the war, where he attended Stanford University. Jerry and Peggy have been residents of Redwood City for sixty years. Jerry worked with Verne Freeman as an accountant at Freeman Paving Company and retired as a Financial Officer of Freeman Sondgroth Construction Company, Inc. in Mountain View. Jerry was a man of rare integrity. He passed on a legacy of strong work ethic, honesty and devotion to his family. He was a man whose life will have an impact for many generations to come. He was a devout Catholic. He and Peggy have been active members of the St. Pius parish for decades. His strong faith, appreciation of nature, love of music, and humor in adversity will long be remembered. Jerry would tell each one of us not to take our health for granted. Friends may visit on Thursday, June 17, 2010 after 5:00 pm and are invited to attend a Vigil Service at 7:00 pm at Crippen & Flynn Woodside Chapel, 400 Woodside Rd., Redwood City. A Funeral Mass will be celebrated on Friday, June 18, 2010 at 10:00 am at St. Pius Catholic Church, 1100 Woodside Rd., Redwood City, with a reception in the church hall at 11:00 am. Interment following at Holy Cross Catholic Cemetery, Menlo Park. In lieu of flowers, the family would welcome donations in Jerry's name to the Redwood City Friends of the Library Program or to Pathways Hospice Foundation.

This article appeared on page Z - 99 of the San Francisco Chronicle

 Cemetery: Holy Cross Catholic Cemetery.

87 Year Old Man Hit By Automobile

An 87 year old man was injured early Friday night when struck by a car as he crossed the intersection of Fifth Street and Olive Avenue, police said.

John B. Lauby 230 Time (possibly Lime?) Avenue, was admitted to St. Mary's Hospital for treatment of minor cuts and bruises and observation. Police cited the driver of the car, Charles Ransom Samuelson, 15, of 4148 Lakewood Drive, for illegal driving with a learner's permit and failing to yield the right of way to a pedestrian. The youth told officers he did not see Lawby until a moment before he struck him.

Lauby was reported in satisfactory contition today.--ancestry.com newspaper collection.
